    {
      "id": "hzlGxrts2IwEBbyUEC0oK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1359.4670899933108,
      "y": 786.35480481557,
      "width": 954.799072265625,
      "height": 160,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b3K",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1717042771,
      "version": 3620,
      "versionNonce": 1946735219,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773696344421,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The main idea for the solution is that the number of elements of the board minus n ( n^ - n ) should be \ngreater or equal the highest number of candies with similar color.\n\nthis way we garantee that we have in minimum three different elements we can put int the diagonal which means \nthe baord can be rearranged. 1\n\nlet c the highest number of candies with similar color. the board can be rearrenged such as no row or column consists of n\n candies of the same color if and only if c <= n^2 - n ",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The main idea for the solution is that the number of elements of the board minus n ( n^ - n ) should be \ngreater or equal the highest number of candies with similar color.\n\nthis way we garantee that we have in minimum three different elements we can put int the diagonal which means \nthe baord can be rearranged. 1\n\nlet c the highest number of candies with similar color. the board can be rearrenged such as no row or column consists of n\n candies of the same color if and only if c <= n^2 - n ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
